Neil James Farnsworth (born 8 May 1977) is an English cricketer.  Farnsworth is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm off break.  He was born in Ashford, Surrey.
Farnsworth represented the Surrey Cricket Board in a single List A cricket match against Shropshire County Cricket Club in the 2000 NatWest Trophy. In his only List A match, he scored 10 runs.He last played club cricket for Ashtead Cricket Club in the Surrey Championship.
